Top ANC deployees have been implicated in corruption linked to the controversial facilities management company Bosasa. ANC spokesperson Dakota Legoete speaks to #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC spokesperson, Dakota Legoete says those implicated in the State Capture Report have a right to take it on review. The party has welcomed the release of part 3 of the report which implicated three senior members. READ: WATCH | Mantashe to take Zondo report on judicial review The ANC has welcomed the release of part 3 of the State Capture Report, which has implicated three senior members. Former President Jacob Zuma, Gwede Mantashe and Nomvula  Mokonyane have been implicated in corruption linked to the controversial facilities management company Bosasa, now known as African Global Operations. Watch the video above for more details on this story.